recital.p:
Following an application from Beghin-Meiji and Tereos Syral, submitted pursuant to Article 13(5) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, the Authority was required to deliver an opinion on a health claim related to short-chain fructooligosaccharides from sucrose and maintenance of normal defecation (Question No EFSA-Q-2015-00377


                        EFSA Journal 2016;14(1):4366.
                  ). The applicant has proposed the following wording for the health claim: 'maintain normal intestinal regularity' or 'maintain intestinal regularity by increasing the frequency of bowel movements' or 'contributes to normal intestinal regularity or normal bowel function'.
